gh pr review 1139 --repo customink/pigment --comment --body "$(cat <<'EOF'
## React Best Practices Review

Overall solid implementation. Clean component structure, good accessibility (focus-visible, aria-hidden, aria-label), proper ref forwarding, ternary conditionals. Four issues worth addressing:

---

### 1. `useImperativeHandle` missing dependency array (Medium)

**`packages/extensions/reco/Atoms/Carousel/Carousel.tsx`**

```tsx
// ❌ Factory runs on every render
React.useImperativeHandle(sliderRef, () => ({
  prev: () => instanceRef.current?.prev(),
  next: () => instanceRef.current?.next(),
}));

// ✅ Stable — instanceRef never changes
React.useImperativeHandle(sliderRef, () => ({
  prev: () => instanceRef.current?.prev(),
  next: () => instanceRef.current?.next(),
}), []);
```

Without `[]`, the handle factory re-runs on every render. Since `instanceRef` is a stable ref, the deps array should be `[]`.

---

### 2. SSR hydration mismatch in `useBreakpoint` (Medium)

**`packages/extensions/reco/hooks/useBreakpoint/useBreakpoint.ts`**

```tsx
// ❌ Server returns 'desktop', client initializes with actual breakpoint → mismatch on mobile/tablet
const [breakpoint, setBreakpoint] = useState<Breakpoint>(() =>
  typeof window !== 'undefined' ? getBreakpoint(window.innerWidth) : 'desktop',
);
```

When SSR renders with `'desktop'` but the client viewport is mobile, React 18 hydration will see a mismatch and throw/warn. Fix: always initialize with the SSR-safe value and update in effect (rule: `rendering-hydration-no-flicker`):

```tsx
// ✅ Consistent SSR/client initial state
const [breakpoint, setBreakpoint] = useState<Breakpoint>('desktop');

useEffect(() => {
  setBreakpoint(getBreakpoint(window.innerWidth));
  const mqMobile = window.matchMedia(`(max-width: ${BREAKPOINTS.mobile - 1}px)`);
  // ...rest of effect
}, []);
```

---

### 3. `ARROW_PATH` imported from Carousel internals (Low)

**`packages/extensions/reco/RecentlyViewedWidget/RecentlyViewedCarousel.tsx`**

```tsx
import { ARROW_PATH } from '../Atoms/Carousel/constants'; // ← reaches into internals
```

`constants.ts` is not re-exported from `Atoms/Carousel/index.ts`, so this imports from an undeclared public API. If Carousel's internals are restructured, this silently breaks. Either export `ARROW_PATH` through `Atoms/Carousel/index.ts` or inline the path in `RecentlyViewedCarousel` (it's used for its own buttons, not the Carousel atom's arrows).

---

### 4. `CardSlide` not memoized (Low)

**`packages/extensions/reco/RecentlyViewedWidget/RecentlyViewedCarousel.tsx`**

`handleCardClick` is correctly memoized, but `CardSlide` itself isn't. On breakpoint change, `RecentlyViewedCarousel` re-renders and all slides re-render even if their props haven't changed. Given `handleCardClick` is already stabilized:

```tsx
const CardSlide = React.memo(function CardSlide({ product, index, onCardClick }: CardSlideProps) {
  ...
});
```

Rule: `rerender-memo`.

---

### 5. Magic breakpoint in CSS diverges from design tokens (Low)

**`packages/extensions/reco/RecentlyViewedWidget/RecentlyViewedCarousel.module.css`**

```css
@media (max-width: 699px) { ... }
```

This hardcodes `699px` while the JS hook derives mobile breakpoint from `units.size.breakpoint.tablet`. If the design token changes, the CSS and JS behavior will drift. Consider deriving this via a CSS custom property or at minimum adding a comment tying it to the token.

EOF
